						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Stone fixed into the wall of the well called Kuṁbāra-bhāvi.</hi></p>						

						<p>16th Century A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record is dated cyclic years <hi rend="bold">Śārvari, Chaitra, ba.</hi> (mistake for s11u.) <hi rend="bold">Paurṇami, Chandrahōre, Pūrvā-nakshatra.</hi> The details cannot be verified. It is in characters of about the <hi rend="bold">16th Century A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription records the construction of a well by Guṇḍayya (?) of <hi rend="bold">Hipparige.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
